1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

2
00:00:09,013 --> 00:00:11,049
Is that key the only clue left?

3
00:00:11,583 --> 00:00:14,352
Tsuda didn't kill your parents.

4
00:00:14,919 --> 00:00:15,753
What?

5
00:00:27,065 --> 00:00:29,033
1995

6
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:31,302
-Hey, I'm scared!
-What?

7
00:00:31,369 --> 00:00:34,072
-Where are we going?
-Just stay quiet and come with me.

8
00:00:34,139 --> 00:00:36,074
-How much farther?
-I don't like this!

9
00:00:36,141 --> 00:00:37,609
Don't open your eyes. Don't.

10
00:00:38,443 --> 00:00:39,777
Okay, now. Open your eyes.

11
00:00:44,616 --> 00:00:46,184
Amazing!

12
00:00:46,251 --> 00:00:48,253
Wow! So pretty!

13
00:00:48,319 --> 00:00:49,154
Right?

14
00:00:49,220 --> 00:00:50,855
It's like a sky of stars!

15
00:00:56,127 --> 00:00:57,595
From time to time,

16
00:00:57,662 --> 00:01:00,365
I would like to eat something light,

17
00:01:00,431 --> 00:01:02,133
not Chinese food all the time!

18
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:03,268
Dad?

19
00:01:12,610 --> 00:01:14,145
Are you looking at them again?

20
00:01:14,946 --> 00:01:17,048
It's not half-bad coming from you, Makoto.

21
00:01:17,115 --> 00:01:18,116
Shut up.

22
00:01:24,289 --> 00:01:25,723
I told you not to take it out.

23
00:01:25,790 --> 00:01:28,359
I never imagined he would
have something like this.

24
00:01:29,761 --> 00:01:31,963
But we aren't even sure it was his yet.

25
00:01:32,030 --> 00:01:34,365
Who else would hide it
in a place like this?

26
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:37,735
Maybe someone else asked him to keep it.

27
00:01:39,704 --> 00:01:40,772
Maybe.

28
00:01:41,906 --> 00:01:43,441
Whether he was just keeping it,

29
00:01:44,642 --> 00:01:46,344
intended to kill with it,

30
00:01:48,213 --> 00:01:50,014
or had already used it…

31
00:01:50,615 --> 00:01:51,282
Stop it.

32
00:01:51,349 --> 00:01:53,518
Not just used,
it's possible he killed with it!

33
00:01:53,585 --> 00:01:54,919
I said stop it!

34
00:02:00,525 --> 00:02:01,893
What do you want to do?

35
00:02:03,328 --> 00:02:05,163
If we investigate further,

36
00:02:06,598 --> 00:02:09,133
we might find out things
we don't want to know.

37
00:02:26,584 --> 00:02:30,321
A group of three robbers
wearing clown masks.

38
00:02:30,388 --> 00:02:32,323
-Scary, huh?
-They went inside?

39
00:02:32,390 --> 00:02:34,125
-Yes.
-I see.

40
00:02:35,727 --> 00:02:37,028
Is something the matter?

41
00:02:38,930 --> 00:02:40,565
Eisuke Ichijo…

42
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:43,968
I killed them.

43
00:02:48,573 --> 00:02:51,843
Around when did the murder take place?

44
00:02:56,014 --> 00:02:58,182
Why did you do that to Mr. Ichijo?

45
00:03:03,621 --> 00:03:07,358
Look, if you stay silent, we won't
know anything, and nothing will progress.

46
00:03:10,662 --> 00:03:11,896
Let's talk again,

47
00:03:12,497 --> 00:03:14,766
once you've calmed down.

48
00:03:22,373 --> 00:03:23,608
He won’t speak at all.

49
00:03:23,675 --> 00:03:26,377
His name is Kenshin Narita, 19 years old.

50
00:03:26,444 --> 00:03:29,647
We confirmed his address
from the ID in his wallet.

51
00:03:29,714 --> 00:03:31,916
But we don't know
his guardian's phone number.

52
00:03:31,983 --> 00:03:34,085
We have no choice
but to go to the address.

53
00:03:34,152 --> 00:03:35,887
It’s probably just a prank anyway.

54
00:03:36,454 --> 00:03:38,723
A death certificate had been filed.

55
00:03:38,790 --> 00:03:41,025
Eisuke Ichijo, 64 years old.

56
00:03:41,092 --> 00:03:44,996
He passed away a month ago, but
it was listed as a cerebral hemorrhage.

57
00:03:45,063 --> 00:03:46,764
Cerebral hemorrhage?

58
00:03:47,332 --> 00:03:49,033
Then it's a natural death, right?

59
00:03:51,569 --> 00:03:54,405
The doctor said it was a natural death!

60
00:03:58,743 --> 00:04:00,178
Dr. Kagura.

61
00:04:00,745 --> 00:04:02,780
Do you have a moment?

62
00:04:02,847 --> 00:04:03,681
Sure.

63
00:04:03,748 --> 00:04:05,750
We were just having a chat.

64
00:04:05,817 --> 00:04:09,654
We were talking excitedly about
gene analysis using nanopore technology.

65
00:04:09,721 --> 00:04:12,156
How do you get excited
over something like that?

66
00:04:12,724 --> 00:04:14,258
This is perfect timing.

67
00:04:14,826 --> 00:04:17,729
Seems Mr. Ichijo was struck
by a terrible headache at work,

68
00:04:17,795 --> 00:04:20,932
went to his usual hospital,
and lost consciousness.

69
00:04:20,998 --> 00:04:24,202
Then, he died from a cerebral hemorrhage.

70
00:04:25,536 --> 00:04:28,740
It seems Mr. Ichijo was being treated
for high blood pressure.

71
00:04:30,541 --> 00:04:34,178
It certainly wouldn't be strange
to rule it a natural death.

72
00:04:35,012 --> 00:04:36,381
Did you hear that?

73
00:04:36,447 --> 00:04:38,449
But, according to the most recent records,

74
00:04:38,516 --> 00:04:40,752
his blood pressure
was actually stabilizing.

75
00:04:40,818 --> 00:04:42,620
Since no autopsy was performed,

76
00:04:42,687 --> 00:04:45,490
things like toxins
can sometimes be overlooked.

77
00:04:45,556 --> 00:04:48,593
I wouldn't say
the possibility of foul play is zero.

78
00:04:52,430 --> 00:04:55,199
Did Kenshin say anything
to you beforehand?

79
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,236
No, nothing.

80
00:04:59,036 --> 00:05:02,206
Do you know anyone
by the name of Eisuke Ichijo?

81
00:05:03,908 --> 00:05:05,276
I don't.

82
00:05:05,843 --> 00:05:08,980
I would like to ask your husband
a few questions as well.

83
00:05:09,046 --> 00:05:13,851
My husband is unwell,
and he has been hospitalized for a while.

84
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:16,354
Enomoto?

85
00:05:16,421 --> 00:05:17,355
TETSU ENOMOTO - TOXICOLOGY

86
00:05:17,422 --> 00:05:18,523
That boy…

87
00:05:18,589 --> 00:05:22,193
his dream was to attend
Professor Enomoto's lectures.

88
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:24,295
At which university?

89
00:05:24,362 --> 00:05:27,064
Jinnan National University.

90
00:05:28,232 --> 00:05:29,534
But this year…

91
00:05:30,101 --> 00:05:32,036
he failed the entrance exam.

92
00:05:32,837 --> 00:05:34,906
I've put him through a lot.

93
00:05:35,907 --> 00:05:38,142
I couldn't afford to send him
to a cram school.

94
00:05:39,510 --> 00:05:40,912
After that, what did he do?

95
00:05:41,612 --> 00:05:46,217
He found a job, but he quit immediately.

96
00:05:47,151 --> 00:05:48,719
Since then,

97
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:52,557
he has spent most of his time in his room.

98
00:05:52,623 --> 00:05:55,059
KENSHIN

99
00:05:56,093 --> 00:05:57,295
Kenshin…

100
00:05:57,895 --> 00:05:59,564
won't be arrested, right?

101
00:06:00,731 --> 00:06:02,900
Narita is pretty smart, isn't he?

102
00:06:02,967 --> 00:06:05,336
Smart enough to take
the Jinnan National University exam.

103
00:06:05,403 --> 00:06:06,270
Jinnan?

104
00:06:06,337 --> 00:06:09,173
Seems he admired Professor Enomoto,
who researches toxins.

105
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,942
-That's why he applied.
-Is that so?

106
00:06:11,008 --> 00:06:12,143
Could it be…

107
00:06:12,710 --> 00:06:14,579
he used poison to commit the murder?

108
00:06:14,645 --> 00:06:17,748
But we haven't found any relation
between him and the victim yet.

109
00:06:17,815 --> 00:06:20,451
-I went to Mr. Ichijo's workplace.
-Well done.

110
00:06:21,085 --> 00:06:24,455
Mr. Ichijo served
as the Chairman of the Board

111
00:06:24,522 --> 00:06:26,457
at Jinnan National University.

112
00:06:27,859 --> 00:06:30,795
The university started using AI
in exam grading this year.

113
00:06:30,862 --> 00:06:33,297
It even made the headlines.

114
00:06:34,065 --> 00:06:36,801
He failed the exam there…

115
00:06:36,868 --> 00:06:39,737
But you wouldn't commit murder
just for failing, would you?

116
00:06:44,742 --> 00:06:47,178
<i>Enomoto is the leading expert</i>
<i>in toxicology.</i>

117
00:06:47,812 --> 00:06:51,048
He would want to attend his lectures
if he wants to pursue that field.

118
00:06:51,582 --> 00:06:54,719
However,
he couldn't afford to retake the exam.

119
00:06:55,653 --> 00:06:58,155
His father’s kidneys failed ten years ago,

120
00:06:58,222 --> 00:07:00,591
and he has been in and out
of the hospital since.

121
00:07:01,092 --> 00:07:02,894
The mother must have it rough.

122
00:07:03,528 --> 00:07:05,663
She cleans a hotel in the morning,

123
00:07:05,730 --> 00:07:08,633
then works at a restaurant
in the same hotel afterward.

124
00:07:08,699 --> 00:07:11,903
Even then, it's barely enough
to take care of the father and son.

125
00:07:12,603 --> 00:07:15,706
That’s why he only applied
to that one university.

126
00:07:16,307 --> 00:07:18,976
Even "safety" schools
require an enrollment fee.

127
00:07:19,043 --> 00:07:21,646
If you don't pay,
your enrollment is voided.

128
00:07:22,914 --> 00:07:25,650
You have to pay
even if you're not sure you'll go there?

129
00:07:27,318 --> 00:07:29,654
Education is on the side of the wealthy.

130
00:07:31,956 --> 00:07:34,525
But… there are exceptions, right?

131
00:07:36,594 --> 00:07:37,762
Minoru.

132
00:07:38,262 --> 00:07:39,630
You did great.

133
00:07:39,697 --> 00:07:41,432
Come on, don't talk about me.

134
00:07:42,567 --> 00:07:44,068
-Makoto.
-Yes?

135
00:07:44,135 --> 00:07:46,938
-Can you take care of the stuff out front?
-What?

136
00:07:51,609 --> 00:07:52,476
Thanks.

137
00:07:57,748 --> 00:07:59,517
Honestly…

138
00:08:00,384 --> 00:08:02,954
I was really surprised
by Minoru back then.

139
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:04,388
We're back to that?

140
00:08:04,455 --> 00:08:08,192
I mean, you suddenly said
you weren't going to take the exams.

141
00:08:08,259 --> 00:08:11,329
I had no choice. We had to make ends meet,

142
00:08:11,395 --> 00:08:14,098
and we didn't have the money
to pay back student loans.

143
00:08:14,632 --> 00:08:17,568
I don't know where he heard it,
but Mogi said,

144
00:08:17,635 --> 00:08:22,139
"If you became an honors student,
your tuition would be waived!"

145
00:08:22,773 --> 00:08:24,842
You sure make it sound easy.

146
00:08:25,443 --> 00:08:26,577
You're drinking?

147
00:08:27,778 --> 00:08:31,115
Being an honors student means being
in the top five out of 3,000 applicants.

148
00:08:32,483 --> 00:08:33,751
-Here.
-Thanks.

149
00:08:37,088 --> 00:08:40,625
He was always telling me
he wanted to go to medical school,

150
00:08:44,295 --> 00:08:46,464
so I just didn't want him to give up.

151
00:08:52,837 --> 00:08:55,406
-Mogi, table for two.
-Welcome.

152
00:08:55,473 --> 00:09:00,378
CHINESE RESTAURANT
MOCCHAN

153
00:09:09,420 --> 00:09:11,922
If I had said
I wanted to be a forensic scientist,

154
00:09:13,124 --> 00:09:14,925
what would Mom and Dad have done?

155
00:09:17,795 --> 00:09:20,898
They would probably have said,
"We don't have that kind of money."

156
00:09:20,965 --> 00:09:23,300
He would have been bragging
to the whole town.

157
00:09:23,934 --> 00:09:24,802
What?

158
00:09:26,937 --> 00:09:29,540
He would find a way to get the money,
no matter what.

159
00:09:34,912 --> 00:09:36,313
Hey, Minoru.

160
00:09:38,683 --> 00:09:40,151
That thing of Dad's.

161
00:09:42,420 --> 00:09:44,755
Should we just throw it into the sea?

162
00:09:54,632 --> 00:09:57,134
Um, about this…

163
00:09:57,902 --> 00:09:59,503
Hey… Excuse me!

164
00:10:00,171 --> 00:10:01,338
-Coming.
-Is anyone--

165
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:05,142
-You never learn, do you?
-No, but…

166
00:10:05,209 --> 00:10:06,644
I have this.

167
00:10:10,548 --> 00:10:11,949
Where did you steal it?

168
00:10:13,384 --> 00:10:15,786
Oh, I just happened to find it.

169
00:10:16,353 --> 00:10:18,222
This isn't yours, right, Asakura?

170
00:10:18,289 --> 00:10:19,423
No, it isn't.

171
00:10:19,490 --> 00:10:21,692
I just picked it up a moment ago.

172
00:10:21,759 --> 00:10:24,095
I actually want to sell this.

173
00:10:28,966 --> 00:10:29,934
Sorry.

174
00:10:36,107 --> 00:10:38,242
So you have no leads at all.

175
00:10:38,943 --> 00:10:39,844
No.

176
00:10:40,377 --> 00:10:42,012
We have one more.

177
00:10:46,417 --> 00:10:48,552
KIRIYADO INN

178
00:10:51,689 --> 00:10:53,290
This is Tsuda's room?

179
00:10:54,058 --> 00:10:57,728
Oh, I'm not sure about the name…

180
00:10:57,795 --> 00:11:01,732
ROOM 2

181
00:11:01,799 --> 00:11:06,103
Whoa, this is terrible.

182
00:11:10,241 --> 00:11:11,609
Tell me the details.

183
00:11:12,243 --> 00:11:13,110
What?

184
00:11:13,944 --> 00:11:15,379
That author's room.

185
00:11:16,313 --> 00:11:18,282
You were in here, weren't you?

186
00:11:18,349 --> 00:11:21,118
23RD LITERARY NONFICTION AWARDS

187
00:11:27,191 --> 00:11:29,293
-Just dropping in.
-Haruko.

188
00:11:30,494 --> 00:11:33,731
It seems this key belonged to the inn
where Tsuda was staying.

189
00:11:35,566 --> 00:11:38,402
The room Tsuda used
was completely trashed.

190
00:11:38,469 --> 00:11:39,403
What?

191
00:11:39,470 --> 00:11:41,438
Maybe he was in debt?

192
00:11:41,505 --> 00:11:44,408
A while ago, some people who looked
like debt collectors showed up.

193
00:11:49,213 --> 00:11:51,582
Hey, where is it?

194
00:11:51,649 --> 00:11:52,817
Hold it right there!

195
00:11:52,883 --> 00:11:54,451
Hey, Tsuda, you bastard!

196
00:11:55,152 --> 00:11:58,189
The injuries Tsuda had were likely
from the assault back then.

197
00:11:58,255 --> 00:11:59,557
Right.

198
00:11:59,623 --> 00:12:02,526
After that, it seems they took
the luggage that was in the room.

199
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:04,195
And…

200
00:12:04,261 --> 00:12:07,765
Tsuda's personal belongings,
stolen before all of that.

201
00:12:07,832 --> 00:12:10,467
Inside were daily necessities and…

202
00:12:11,135 --> 00:12:12,369
these documents.

203
00:12:15,372 --> 00:12:17,942
The procurement list
for Karashima Metal Industries.

204
00:12:21,345 --> 00:12:23,047
Why would he have that?

205
00:12:24,181 --> 00:12:25,282
I knew it.

206
00:12:25,783 --> 00:12:28,219
Tsuda really was snooping
around the factory.

207
00:12:29,486 --> 00:12:30,588
But…

208
00:12:30,654 --> 00:12:32,990
I don't think it has anything
to do with that case.

209
00:12:35,292 --> 00:12:38,062
STAINLESS STEEL / WASHER
NUTS / IRON PIPE

210
00:12:41,999 --> 00:12:43,467
I heard from Minoru.

211
00:12:45,636 --> 00:12:47,638
I didn't really want to hear it, though.

212
00:12:48,205 --> 00:12:50,441
Haruko, can I leave it to you?

213
00:12:52,476 --> 00:12:54,678
There are things
you're better off not knowing.

214
00:12:58,249 --> 00:12:59,650
I'll be in touch.

215
00:13:13,530 --> 00:13:14,832
What did you ask for?

216
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:17,668
Nothing.

217
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:27,711
Huh? You're…

218
00:13:29,313 --> 00:13:30,180
What's wrong?

219
00:13:45,129 --> 00:13:46,330
It’s no use.

220
00:13:46,397 --> 00:13:47,865
He won't look me in the eye.

221
00:13:47,932 --> 00:13:50,801
You never know
what smart guys are thinking.

222
00:13:50,868 --> 00:13:52,102
Tagusari.

223
00:13:52,836 --> 00:13:54,772
-I'm counting on you.
-What?

224
00:13:54,838 --> 00:13:55,739
Go on.

225
00:14:12,423 --> 00:14:14,792
He has been like this since yesterday.

226
00:14:17,828 --> 00:14:20,230
He would be a good match
for my little brother.

227
00:14:23,667 --> 00:14:25,002
But…

228
00:14:26,303 --> 00:14:29,540
Inside that head of yours,
you're probably thinking hard.

229
00:14:30,407 --> 00:14:33,877
You line up all the possibilities
and pick the best choice.

230
00:14:34,645 --> 00:14:36,613
This time, it was turning yourself in.

231
00:14:39,116 --> 00:14:40,617
You have a hidden agenda, don't you?

232
00:14:40,684 --> 00:14:42,419
Hold on. Mr. Tagusari.

233
00:14:44,555 --> 00:14:46,590
His mother will be here soon.

234
00:14:47,358 --> 00:14:49,126
Should we try asking your mom?

235
00:14:50,294 --> 00:14:52,529
Please don't be so harsh to my mother.

236
00:14:54,832 --> 00:14:58,402
Since I failed the exam,
she's been unwell.

237
00:15:03,841 --> 00:15:06,543
You really had no idea at all?

238
00:15:06,610 --> 00:15:07,845
No.

239
00:15:07,911 --> 00:15:11,682
It seems he left the house
while I was at work.

240
00:15:13,017 --> 00:15:14,351
I see.

241
00:15:14,885 --> 00:15:18,555
Well then, please try talking
with Kenshin one more time.

242
00:15:19,623 --> 00:15:20,691
I'm very sorry.

243
00:15:25,863 --> 00:15:27,531
What do you think?

244
00:15:28,899 --> 00:15:33,103
Do you think he killed the Chairman
out of a grudge for failing the exam?

245
00:15:33,170 --> 00:15:34,171
Mr. Tagusari.

246
00:15:35,739 --> 00:15:38,375
He's not the kind of boy
who would do such a thing.

247
00:15:40,978 --> 00:15:42,146
I just…

248
00:15:43,347 --> 00:15:45,082
I can't accept it.

249
00:15:46,016 --> 00:15:50,120
In his own self-grading,
he definitely had a passing grade.

250
00:15:51,121 --> 00:15:52,756
It must be some kind of mistake.

251
00:15:57,461 --> 00:15:59,797
ICHIJO

252
00:16:01,498 --> 00:16:02,332
<i>Yes?</i>

253
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:06,437
Is this the residence of Mr. Ichijo,
Chairman of Jinnan National University?

254
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:13,777
CCTV footage has already been overwritten.

255
00:16:13,844 --> 00:16:15,746
It has been a month, after all.

256
00:16:18,015 --> 00:16:22,953
On the day your husband passed away,
was he acting strange in any way?

257
00:16:23,821 --> 00:16:27,658
He was tired from work,
but he went to the university as usual…

258
00:16:28,926 --> 00:16:33,664
I still can't accept it,
so the room is exactly as it was that day.

259
00:16:34,364 --> 00:16:35,899
How's it going on your end?

260
00:16:35,966 --> 00:16:38,569
It's tough, there are few cameras
around the complex.

261
00:16:38,635 --> 00:16:42,239
We can't confirm Kenshin Narita
left his home on the day of the murder.

262
00:16:42,306 --> 00:16:43,907
No luck with the Chairman either.

263
00:16:43,974 --> 00:16:46,477
It was all very sudden.

264
00:16:46,543 --> 00:16:49,146
His belongings hadn't been organized yet.

265
00:16:52,883 --> 00:16:54,885
You're going to Haruko's place, right?

266
00:16:55,385 --> 00:16:56,787
I already contacted her.

267
00:16:57,287 --> 00:16:58,922
You know her number?

268
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:02,459
Online posts?

269
00:17:03,026 --> 00:17:04,161
After the results got out,

270
00:17:04,228 --> 00:17:07,598
there were quite a few applicants making
the same claim as Kenshin.

271
00:17:08,165 --> 00:17:11,168
They said that by their own grading,
they should have passed.

272
00:17:11,668 --> 00:17:12,970
IT'S BECAUSE OF THE AI, ISN'T IT?

273
00:17:13,036 --> 00:17:14,872
The grading was done by AI.

274
00:17:15,973 --> 00:17:18,041
Things do seem fishy here.

275
00:17:18,709 --> 00:17:19,810
Do you know something?

276
00:17:20,410 --> 00:17:23,380
This university is unusually
close to the Ministry of Education.

277
00:17:24,114 --> 00:17:26,783
Even though operating grants
are trending downward,

278
00:17:26,850 --> 00:17:28,919
they're receiving nearly 60 billion yen.

279
00:17:28,986 --> 00:17:30,354
60 billion?

280
00:17:31,221 --> 00:17:33,357
Okay. I'll look into it a bit.

281
00:17:33,423 --> 00:17:36,093
Can you carry this stuff
to the front of my shop?

282
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:36,994
What?

283
00:17:38,328 --> 00:17:39,196
Please!

284
00:17:39,263 --> 00:17:40,764
Wait, hold on.

285
00:17:42,499 --> 00:17:43,433
I'm hungry.

286
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:44,835
What should we eat?

287
00:17:56,246 --> 00:17:58,549
Eat this. It's really good.

288
00:18:00,384 --> 00:18:02,786
-Yummy!
-Right?

289
00:18:08,392 --> 00:18:09,493
Haruko, you…

290
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:10,394
Yes?

291
00:18:11,061 --> 00:18:14,431
You're so good at your job,
so why run a pawn shop?

292
00:18:17,367 --> 00:18:18,802
Originally, that place

293
00:18:19,903 --> 00:18:22,773
was the shop of an informant
I used when I was a reporter.

294
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:27,010
Then they got sick and were looking
for someone to take over.

295
00:18:28,212 --> 00:18:30,214
So that's why you quit being a reporter.

296
00:18:31,715 --> 00:18:36,086
Exposing people's secrets
isn't exactly a pleasant thing, is it?

297
00:18:37,955 --> 00:18:39,089
For example,

298
00:18:39,156 --> 00:18:44,094
there are things that family members
are better off not knowing.

299
00:18:46,563 --> 00:18:48,699
I was thinking about such things,

300
00:18:49,466 --> 00:18:51,068
so I decided to take over.

301
00:18:53,804 --> 00:18:56,740
The police can't look at it that way.

302
00:18:57,774 --> 00:18:58,909
I suppose not.

303
00:19:01,311 --> 00:19:05,782
It's just that, to me,
"the truth" was a little too dazzling.

304
00:19:24,167 --> 00:19:26,536
Rare to see you like this.
You aren't drinking?

305
00:19:26,603 --> 00:19:27,838
Yes.

306
00:19:28,538 --> 00:19:30,407
I was a bit tired, so I was resting.

307
00:19:31,108 --> 00:19:32,676
At least take off your jacket.

308
00:19:33,477 --> 00:19:34,845
I guess you're right.

309
00:19:39,549 --> 00:19:41,718
That applicant turned himself in
again today.

310
00:19:42,219 --> 00:19:43,153
Again?

311
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,589
We thought he would finally speak,

312
00:19:45,656 --> 00:19:47,591
but he just said
he's worried about his mom.

313
00:19:48,692 --> 00:19:51,995
You never know
what smart guys are thinking.

314
00:19:55,232 --> 00:19:56,199
Did something happen?

315
00:19:57,234 --> 00:19:58,602
What do you mean?

316
00:19:58,669 --> 00:20:00,837
You’ve been like this
since you were a kid.

317
00:20:00,904 --> 00:20:04,308
Whenever you hide something in a hurry,
you put it in the microwave.

318
00:20:04,374 --> 00:20:05,542
Minoru!

319
00:20:11,581 --> 00:20:12,916
Is this from Haruko?

320
00:20:13,784 --> 00:20:15,252
I told you to drop it.

321
00:20:16,019 --> 00:20:17,220
I had her look into info

322
00:20:17,287 --> 00:20:20,824
about guns used in the vicinity
of Yomogida Town 30 years ago.

323
00:20:26,163 --> 00:20:28,432
Between 1990 and 1995…

324
00:20:28,999 --> 00:20:32,869
the five years before Dad was killed,
there were two shootings in Kanagawa.

325
00:20:32,936 --> 00:20:34,104
Shooting incidents?

326
00:20:34,171 --> 00:20:36,273
The culprit wasn't caught in either case.

327
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:38,608
But in one of them, someone died.

328
00:20:38,675 --> 00:20:39,576
Who was killed?

329
00:20:39,643 --> 00:20:40,377
GUNSHOT HEARD

330
00:20:40,444 --> 00:20:41,845
Kaga Shokichi.

331
00:20:41,912 --> 00:20:44,214
An old guy who ran
a tatami shop in Yomogida Town.

332
00:20:44,281 --> 00:20:45,515
Was he connected to Dad?

333
00:20:46,149 --> 00:20:47,184
I don't know.

334
00:20:47,684 --> 00:20:50,887
Where is that tatami shop?
Do we know anyone related to Kaga?

335
00:20:50,954 --> 00:20:53,824
It was 30 years ago.
That shop is an apartment building now.

336
00:20:55,292 --> 00:20:56,126
But…

337
00:20:56,860 --> 00:20:58,795
This might be completely unrelated.

338
00:20:58,862 --> 00:20:59,963
Or…

339
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:01,665
Dad might have killed him.

340
00:21:02,499 --> 00:21:05,035
-That can't be--
-That’s why I told you to stop!

341
00:21:08,438 --> 00:21:09,639
In the end,

342
00:21:10,440 --> 00:21:11,742
it’s all just speculation.

343
00:21:30,460 --> 00:21:31,395
Section Chief.

344
00:21:32,095 --> 00:21:33,630
Did Narita finally say something?

345
00:21:33,697 --> 00:21:34,598
No, I'm…

346
00:21:35,165 --> 00:21:37,334
A colleague asked for some advice.

347
00:21:37,401 --> 00:21:38,235
Yes?

348
00:21:38,301 --> 00:21:39,336
About 30 years ago,

349
00:21:39,403 --> 00:21:41,972
there were two shootings in Kanagawa,
do you remember?

350
00:21:42,572 --> 00:21:44,708
Yes, the culprit was never caught.

351
00:21:44,775 --> 00:21:47,277
You were at the Yomogida Station
back then, right?

352
00:21:47,778 --> 00:21:48,979
Do you have any info?

353
00:21:51,548 --> 00:21:53,083
Why ask about such an old case?

354
00:21:54,418 --> 00:21:56,720
It's related to a case
my colleague is chasing.

355
00:21:59,222 --> 00:22:00,524
Which police station?

356
00:22:02,793 --> 00:22:04,461
Totsuka North Station.

357
00:22:04,528 --> 00:22:05,662
Here you go.

358
00:22:07,831 --> 00:22:10,834
Sorry for bothering you so many times.

359
00:22:12,235 --> 00:22:13,537
And today?

360
00:22:14,671 --> 00:22:15,906
What's wrong?

361
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:19,609
Do you still have the documents
from the factory?

362
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:21,511
From the factory?

363
00:22:22,012 --> 00:22:25,215
A robot my dad made for me broke,

364
00:22:25,282 --> 00:22:28,485
and to repair it,
I need to know the metal he used.

365
00:22:30,253 --> 00:22:31,855
You could take it to a professional.

366
00:22:32,456 --> 00:22:35,325
It's handmade by my dad,
so I want to try fixing it myself.

367
00:22:39,196 --> 00:22:40,163
I see.

368
00:22:41,231 --> 00:22:43,133
I'll go take a look.

369
00:23:24,641 --> 00:23:26,009
1995 KARASHIMA METAL FACTORY

370
00:23:26,076 --> 00:23:28,211
TAX OFFICE

371
00:23:31,248 --> 00:23:32,382
What are you doing?

372
00:23:35,418 --> 00:23:36,386
Those…

373
00:23:38,154 --> 00:23:40,123
belong to our tax accountant.

374
00:23:49,165 --> 00:23:52,602
They were lying here on the floor,
so I was trying to tidy them up.

375
00:23:53,436 --> 00:23:54,538
Lying on the floor?

376
00:24:07,984 --> 00:24:10,954
I must have left it open again.

377
00:24:19,396 --> 00:24:20,430
Hey.

378
00:24:20,497 --> 00:24:21,865
Where are you going?

379
00:24:24,568 --> 00:24:27,270
Is someone involved
in the grading error coming here?

380
00:24:27,337 --> 00:24:28,371
Kudo.

381
00:24:28,905 --> 00:24:31,875
Did you forget your badge
at the place we drank at yesterday?

382
00:24:31,942 --> 00:24:32,909
What?

383
00:24:35,045 --> 00:24:36,680
I have it here…

384
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:39,249
So you believed me?

385
00:24:40,650 --> 00:24:42,385
Are you back to being a reporter?

386
00:24:43,286 --> 00:24:44,220
Just helping out.

387
00:24:45,221 --> 00:24:46,823
Who is this person?

388
00:24:46,890 --> 00:24:48,825
Probably someone
from the Ministry of Education.

389
00:24:52,095 --> 00:24:55,932
This is a chance to drag
the higher-ups down.

390
00:24:58,935 --> 00:25:02,372
These are communication records
between our Bureau Chief and Ichijo.

391
00:25:05,976 --> 00:25:12,082
PHARMACY

392
00:25:20,924 --> 00:25:22,325
TITLE: "ABOUT THE GRADING ERRORS"

393
00:25:22,392 --> 00:25:24,160
As a university,

394
00:25:24,227 --> 00:25:26,796
they couldn't afford
to admit a grading error.

395
00:25:28,665 --> 00:25:31,835
<i>Could it be</i>
<i>that Jinnan National University,</i>

396
00:25:31,901 --> 00:25:35,905
<i>which introduced AI grading last year,</i>
<i>has covered up a grading error?</i>

397
00:25:35,972 --> 00:25:38,408
<i>An insider investigation revealed</i>
<i>new developments.</i>

398
00:25:39,175 --> 00:25:42,512
<i>There are also suspicions</i>
<i>of illegal monetary transactions</i>

399
00:25:42,579 --> 00:25:45,215
<i>between the university</i>
<i>and the Ministry of Education.</i>

400
00:25:45,882 --> 00:25:48,852
<i>-The Ministry vowed to look into…</i>
-The Ministry is involved too.

401
00:25:49,519 --> 00:25:52,322
They've already decided
on a successor for the Bureau Chief.

402
00:25:52,389 --> 00:25:54,624
They really moved fast.

403
00:25:55,125 --> 00:25:59,229
But the details of the cover-up
haven't been reported by the media.

404
00:26:00,864 --> 00:26:03,600
Our Section Chief is pestering
the higher-ups for answers.

405
00:26:04,434 --> 00:26:06,469
They say the cause was human error.

406
00:26:06,970 --> 00:26:08,004
Human error?

407
00:26:08,071 --> 00:26:09,205
It seems a mistake occurred

408
00:26:09,272 --> 00:26:12,776
when staff were manually inputting
the AI's grading results.

409
00:26:13,343 --> 00:26:15,812
And the Chairman,
Mr. Ichijo, covered it up?

410
00:26:15,879 --> 00:26:19,082
Yes, so their illegal subsidies
from the Ministry would continue.

411
00:26:20,216 --> 00:26:23,553
Mr. Koike, can you go
to Narita's house one more time?

412
00:26:42,739 --> 00:26:43,807
What is it?

413
00:26:43,873 --> 00:26:45,375
It's about the Narita case.

414
00:26:46,376 --> 00:26:48,078
Something feels off to me.

415
00:26:48,912 --> 00:26:50,280
You too, Minoru?

416
00:26:50,847 --> 00:26:54,617
<i>If the goal was to expose the cover-up,</i>
<i>there's no need for him to stay silent.</i>

417
00:26:55,251 --> 00:26:58,555
And turning yourself in when
you didn't kill anyone is too high a risk.

418
00:26:59,122 --> 00:27:01,958
I feel like we're being led
by Kenshin Narita.

419
00:27:02,726 --> 00:27:04,694
I don't like this.

420
00:27:06,329 --> 00:27:08,765
What about Jinnan National University?

421
00:27:09,265 --> 00:27:11,067
I saw it on the news.

422
00:27:12,102 --> 00:27:13,770
Did you know about it too, ma'am?

423
00:27:16,573 --> 00:27:20,443
Kenshin went to us in hopes
that the police would expose it.

424
00:27:20,510 --> 00:27:21,544
Ishizaka.

425
00:27:24,514 --> 00:27:26,149
Oh, excuse me.

426
00:27:28,051 --> 00:27:29,285
Yes?

427
00:27:29,352 --> 00:27:31,287
Oh, Mr. Tagusari.

428
00:27:33,790 --> 00:27:34,858
I'm coming in.

429
00:27:47,937 --> 00:27:49,739
Did it go as you planned?

430
00:27:54,511 --> 00:27:56,212
Someone gave me an assessment.

431
00:27:57,180 --> 00:27:59,215
They pointed out that Mr. Ichijo's murder

432
00:27:59,282 --> 00:28:02,485
might have been carried out
with a Green Mamba.

433
00:28:04,254 --> 00:28:05,622
It's a venomous snake.

434
00:28:05,688 --> 00:28:06,956
A venomous snake?

435
00:28:07,023 --> 00:28:08,158
Speak truthfully.

436
00:28:08,658 --> 00:28:11,161
-If you did it, you have to atone for it.
-Stop it.

437
00:28:11,227 --> 00:28:13,163
Venom is not a tool for murder.

438
00:28:15,665 --> 00:28:17,400
Green Mamba toxins

439
00:28:17,467 --> 00:28:20,770
are being researched as a treatment
for several incurable diseases.

440
00:28:20,837 --> 00:28:22,906
And scorpion toxins

441
00:28:22,972 --> 00:28:25,508
may be used to make
more eco-friendly pesticides.

442
00:28:25,575 --> 00:28:28,945
Venom has the potential
to change the future.

443
00:28:38,021 --> 00:28:39,222
By the way,

444
00:28:40,156 --> 00:28:44,227
when death occurs from Green Mamba venom,
the respiratory muscles are paralyzed,

445
00:28:44,861 --> 00:28:46,863
leading to respiratory arrest.

446
00:28:48,565 --> 00:28:51,835
That's different from
the Chairman's cause of death.

447
00:28:56,906 --> 00:28:59,742
Narita hasn't given up
on toxicology yet, huh.

448
00:29:01,244 --> 00:29:04,514
The Green Mamba is the snake
Professor Enomoto is researching.

449
00:29:05,014 --> 00:29:07,517
<i>He hasn't gotten rid</i>
<i>of his study materials,</i>

450
00:29:07,584 --> 00:29:08,818
so while he was cooped up…

451
00:29:08,885 --> 00:29:10,620
He kept up his studies?

452
00:29:13,189 --> 00:29:15,825
We can't progress.
Let's end the investigation here.

453
00:29:15,892 --> 00:29:16,926
Wait.

454
00:29:17,527 --> 00:29:19,796
Narita went out of his way
to turn himself in.

455
00:29:19,863 --> 00:29:22,665
But why would he kill
if he still plans to take the exam?

456
00:29:22,732 --> 00:29:25,101
But, there might be something.

457
00:29:25,168 --> 00:29:26,903
We won't find out anything.

458
00:29:26,970 --> 00:29:28,471
Not from the son.

459
00:29:29,472 --> 00:29:30,740
What do you mean?

460
00:29:31,241 --> 00:29:33,509
Aside from talking about the murder,

461
00:29:33,576 --> 00:29:36,145
Narita only talked
about toxins and his mother.

462
00:29:36,212 --> 00:29:40,016
Those two things are likely
what he treasures most.

463
00:29:41,417 --> 00:29:42,652
Let's say he was trying…

464
00:29:44,087 --> 00:29:46,189
to protect one of them, his mother.

465
00:29:46,789 --> 00:29:50,894
-He's trying to take the blame for her?
-He knew we couldn't charge him.

466
00:29:51,461 --> 00:29:55,431
And the police would also expose
the university's cover-up.

467
00:29:55,999 --> 00:29:58,067
I confirmed it with Mr. Ichijo's wife.

468
00:29:58,768 --> 00:30:01,271
After the results were announced,
the mother, Atsuko,

469
00:30:01,337 --> 00:30:03,873
visited Mr. Ichijo's home several times.

470
00:30:03,940 --> 00:30:05,909
So the two knew each other after all.

471
00:30:05,975 --> 00:30:08,344
It's about her son.
The mother has a motive.

472
00:30:08,912 --> 00:30:10,780
Even so, we can't make an arrest.

473
00:30:10,847 --> 00:30:11,981
Section Chief.

474
00:30:12,615 --> 00:30:14,350
We also have other cases.

475
00:30:14,417 --> 00:30:17,520
One more day. If no evidence
comes up, we’re closing this.

476
00:30:18,154 --> 00:30:18,988
Okay.

477
00:30:21,791 --> 00:30:23,326
One more day…

478
00:30:23,393 --> 00:30:26,462
Mrs. Narita is a really hard worker.

479
00:30:27,063 --> 00:30:30,800
As soon as she finishes cleaning,
she starts at the first-floor restaurant.

480
00:30:30,867 --> 00:30:33,002
When did she start this routine?

481
00:30:33,703 --> 00:30:34,804
A month ago.

482
00:30:34,871 --> 00:30:37,507
She quit her daytime job
and started at the restaurant.

483
00:30:37,573 --> 00:30:42,078
She was already working the cleaning job,
so I guess commuting was hard.

484
00:30:42,879 --> 00:30:45,415
Do you know what her daytime job was?

485
00:30:46,382 --> 00:30:47,850
A pharmacist.

486
00:30:47,917 --> 00:30:49,719
Near Aoki General Hospital.

487
00:30:49,786 --> 00:30:54,223
Narita's mother dispensed medication
at the pharmacy Mr. Ichijo frequented.

488
00:30:54,290 --> 00:30:57,293
For hypertension,
I believe he was taking antiplatelet drugs

489
00:30:57,360 --> 00:30:59,996
to suppress platelet activity.

490
00:31:00,063 --> 00:31:02,899
Can other drugs cause
a cerebral hemorrhage?

491
00:31:04,600 --> 00:31:06,102
Maybe NSAIDs?

492
00:31:06,169 --> 00:31:07,403
What are those?

493
00:31:08,004 --> 00:31:11,541
Drugs that suppress inflammation
and reduce pain.

494
00:31:12,475 --> 00:31:13,609
If used together,

495
00:31:13,676 --> 00:31:17,413
platelet function decreases further,
increasing the risk of bleeding,

496
00:31:18,114 --> 00:31:20,216
and blood vessels
in the brain can rupture.

497
00:31:22,819 --> 00:31:25,621
Did the mother kill him
by exploiting a drug interaction?

498
00:31:25,688 --> 00:31:27,323
First, we need evidence.

499
00:31:28,057 --> 00:31:30,593
The pharmacy's security footage is gone.

500
00:31:30,660 --> 00:31:32,929
What if we check the NSAID inventory?

501
00:31:32,996 --> 00:31:35,565
Even if there's a discrepancy in sales,

502
00:31:35,631 --> 00:31:39,002
it's not proof that Narita's mother
mixed them in.

503
00:31:45,241 --> 00:31:46,376
The medicine bag?

504
00:31:48,144 --> 00:31:51,681
If NSAIDs are found in the bag
prescribed to Mr. Ichijo, it's evidence!

505
00:31:52,782 --> 00:31:53,649
Kudo.

506
00:31:55,618 --> 00:31:58,221
It has been a month.
Something like that is already--

507
00:31:58,287 --> 00:32:01,090
His wife still kept his belongings.

508
00:32:01,157 --> 00:32:02,992
<i>It was all very sudden.</i>

509
00:32:03,559 --> 00:32:05,728
<i>His belongings hadn't been organized yet.</i>

510
00:32:08,364 --> 00:32:10,466
She moved away after the cover-up report!

511
00:32:10,533 --> 00:32:12,301
Seems she just finished packing.

512
00:32:12,368 --> 00:32:13,536
Then the medicine too?

513
00:32:15,438 --> 00:32:17,206
It has probably been collected.

514
00:32:17,273 --> 00:32:20,043
Trash collection in their district
should be around 12 p.m.

515
00:32:20,109 --> 00:32:21,411
Fifteen minutes left.

516
00:32:34,690 --> 00:32:35,892
Wait a moment!

517
00:32:35,958 --> 00:32:36,959
Wait!

518
00:32:37,026 --> 00:32:39,996
I'm Kudo from Aoi Station.
Can you help with our investigation?

519
00:32:40,063 --> 00:32:44,000
REMEMBER TO PUT A NET COVERING YOUR TRASH

520
00:32:47,837 --> 00:32:49,005
Mrs. Narita.

521
00:32:49,639 --> 00:32:52,942
Sorry for coming at such a late hour.
May we have a word?

522
00:32:55,711 --> 00:32:57,146
What is it?

523
00:32:58,815 --> 00:33:01,217
The one who killed Eisuke Ichijo

524
00:33:02,051 --> 00:33:03,019
was you, wasn't it?

525
00:33:05,521 --> 00:33:06,722
A month ago,

526
00:33:06,789 --> 00:33:09,492
you visited Mr. Ichijo's home
several times.

527
00:33:10,693 --> 00:33:13,229
You found out about the grading cover-up

528
00:33:13,296 --> 00:33:16,032
and went to demand they grant him
admission, didn't you?

529
00:33:19,402 --> 00:33:23,739
His wife saw you confronting Mr. Ichijo.

530
00:33:27,610 --> 00:33:28,444
But…

531
00:33:30,113 --> 00:33:32,181
he wouldn't take you seriously.

532
00:33:36,119 --> 00:33:39,722
It seems you've known
Mr. Ichijo for a while.

533
00:33:42,492 --> 00:33:44,894
Mr. Ichijo had his prescriptions
filled regularly

534
00:33:44,961 --> 00:33:48,030
at the pharmacy where you worked.

535
00:33:48,097 --> 00:33:51,534
And so you mixed NSAIDs
into the antiplatelet medication

536
00:33:51,601 --> 00:33:53,236
which he took daily,

537
00:33:53,870 --> 00:33:55,671
killing him.

538
00:34:06,816 --> 00:34:08,050
The entrance exam

539
00:34:09,685 --> 00:34:11,854
was important to both your son and you.

540
00:34:14,924 --> 00:34:17,126
Ever since your husband got sick,

541
00:34:18,127 --> 00:34:22,331
the two of you have been
working hard together, in that room.

542
00:34:25,635 --> 00:34:29,505
<i>You must have been desperately</i>
<i>doing what you could to support Kenshin.</i>

543
00:34:29,572 --> 00:34:31,240
TO KENSHIN

544
00:34:31,807 --> 00:34:33,309
<i>Because of your circumstances,</i>

545
00:34:33,910 --> 00:34:36,212
<i>you couldn't even send him to cram school.</i>

546
00:34:37,446 --> 00:34:39,115
<i>Due to that guilt,</i>

547
00:34:40,249 --> 00:34:42,585
<i>you wanted him to pass no matter what.</i>

548
00:34:47,657 --> 00:34:48,658
That’s why…

549
00:34:49,892 --> 00:34:52,228
you couldn't forgive Mr. Ichijo

550
00:34:53,596 --> 00:34:55,464
for stealing your son's future.

551
00:34:58,534 --> 00:34:59,569
But…

552
00:35:02,905 --> 00:35:04,307
nothing changed.

553
00:35:06,676 --> 00:35:08,511
<i>All that was left was regret.</i>

554
00:35:09,679 --> 00:35:11,447
<i>I'm going to the police.</i>

555
00:35:14,717 --> 00:35:15,751
I'm sorry.

556
00:35:18,221 --> 00:35:19,255
Sorry.

557
00:35:23,326 --> 00:35:24,160
Mom…

558
00:35:28,864 --> 00:35:30,366
I'll go.

559
00:35:31,601 --> 00:35:32,635
What?

560
00:35:32,702 --> 00:35:36,539
If I say I killed him,
the police will look into it, right?

561
00:35:39,208 --> 00:35:40,776
What do you think

562
00:35:41,711 --> 00:35:44,347
was the thing Kenshin
really wanted to protect?

563
00:35:52,088 --> 00:35:53,956
If he failed the exam,

564
00:35:55,758 --> 00:35:58,628
surely you would never stop
blaming yourself.

565
00:36:00,062 --> 00:36:02,732
He wanted to prove one thing
by exposing the cover-up.

566
00:36:04,300 --> 00:36:06,002
That even without money,

567
00:36:06,969 --> 00:36:08,638
he can beat the exams.

568
00:36:11,307 --> 00:36:13,809
That the time he spent
working hard with his mother…

569
00:36:16,045 --> 00:36:17,647
wasn't a mistake.

570
00:36:23,653 --> 00:36:24,720
That’s why,

571
00:36:26,589 --> 00:36:29,458
you would do anything
for the sake of the exam.

572
00:36:31,027 --> 00:36:32,061
Even if it meant

573
00:36:33,763 --> 00:36:36,432
committing an irreversible sin.

574
00:37:20,776 --> 00:37:21,677
But…

575
00:37:22,778 --> 00:37:24,213
all of this is speculation.

576
00:37:24,914 --> 00:37:26,916
There's no evidence.

577
00:37:30,152 --> 00:37:32,955
We don't know how
you discovered the cover-up,

578
00:37:33,656 --> 00:37:35,691
and the bag of mixed medicine

579
00:37:35,758 --> 00:37:37,893
was already taken
by the garbage collectors.

580
00:37:40,496 --> 00:37:43,999
Besides, since it doesn't
always lead to death,

581
00:37:44,066 --> 00:37:45,634
maybe you only meant…

582
00:37:47,536 --> 00:37:49,705
to make him suffer, not kill him.

583
00:37:53,809 --> 00:37:55,611
The investigation ends today.

584
00:37:58,781 --> 00:38:02,718
We can no longer arrest the culprit.

585
00:38:14,463 --> 00:38:15,931
Can we talk for a second?

586
00:38:33,082 --> 00:38:35,951
This is your exam paper,
graded by an expert.

587
00:38:43,626 --> 00:38:45,628
Believing in your passing,

588
00:38:46,929 --> 00:38:48,931
your mother committed a crime.

589
00:38:52,601 --> 00:38:54,170
If you're going to hide it from her,

590
00:38:56,038 --> 00:38:57,706
hide it until the day you die.

591
00:39:02,278 --> 00:39:05,214
TOTAL SCORE: 880
RESULT: FAILED

592
00:39:06,449 --> 00:39:07,750
No way…

593
00:39:16,292 --> 00:39:17,993
I couldn't do it after all.

594
00:39:21,597 --> 00:39:24,300
Education is on the side
of the wealthy, apparently.

595
00:39:25,668 --> 00:39:26,635
<i>Though…</i>

596
00:39:28,103 --> 00:39:31,006
<i>I do know someone who overcame that.</i>

597
00:39:37,346 --> 00:39:39,882
MAKOTO TAGUSARI

598
00:40:01,003 --> 00:40:04,006
Mr. Ichijo also had a family
who loved him.

599
00:40:04,607 --> 00:40:07,776
If you ever feel like talking,
please contact us anytime.

600
00:40:29,198 --> 00:40:31,734
Did you want to arrest
that mother and son so badly?

601
00:40:34,103 --> 00:40:34,970
No.

602
00:40:35,704 --> 00:40:37,873
The one I'm stuck on is the mother.

603
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:39,275
The mother?

604
00:40:39,341 --> 00:40:41,877
I saw a TeleSeek notification
on her phone.

605
00:40:42,478 --> 00:40:45,047
That app that doesn't store
message history?

606
00:40:45,681 --> 00:40:48,250
A mom wouldn't normally use
something like that.

607
00:40:48,918 --> 00:40:51,587
She lives with her son,
so she wouldn't need it anyway.

608
00:40:52,087 --> 00:40:52,922
That's true.

609
00:40:56,492 --> 00:40:58,394
It just leaves a bad taste in my mouth.

610
00:41:00,963 --> 00:41:02,665
I have a bad taste in my mouth too.

611
00:41:04,934 --> 00:41:06,969
You went out of your way to call me here

612
00:41:07,036 --> 00:41:09,305
to try and convince me
about Dad, didn't you?

613
00:41:10,205 --> 00:41:12,808
Even though you'll keep going
by yourself, anyway.

614
00:41:15,144 --> 00:41:16,378
That kind of thing

615
00:41:17,346 --> 00:41:18,881
really pisses me off.

616
00:41:26,889 --> 00:41:28,290
Did you find out anything?

617
00:41:29,792 --> 00:41:32,094
You were also poking around
by yourself, right?

618
00:41:35,764 --> 00:41:37,333
I went to the tax accountant's office.

619
00:41:38,601 --> 00:41:40,736
I compared the procurement list Tsuda had

620
00:41:40,803 --> 00:41:44,239
with the subsidiary ledger
from the Karashima Metal factory.

621
00:41:46,775 --> 00:41:48,911
In the subsidiary ledger
for the tax return,

622
00:41:49,445 --> 00:41:51,680
one type of metal had been erased.

623
00:41:52,581 --> 00:41:53,682
Erased?

624
00:41:55,618 --> 00:41:57,152
In Tsuda's procurement list,

625
00:41:57,653 --> 00:41:59,421
there was SNCM.

626
00:42:00,055 --> 00:42:03,058
This metal is used for jet engine turbines

627
00:42:03,125 --> 00:42:04,994
and valves in oil equipment.

628
00:42:05,628 --> 00:42:06,528
As well as…

629
00:42:08,364 --> 00:42:09,431
handguns.

630
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:14,036
That gun might not
have been meant for use,

631
00:42:14,103 --> 00:42:16,605
but rather something
manufactured at the factory.

632
00:42:19,775 --> 00:42:20,876
I see.

633
00:42:24,079 --> 00:42:25,514
The pieces might be coming together.

634
00:42:28,283 --> 00:42:29,652
I asked the Section Chief,

635
00:42:29,718 --> 00:42:33,422
and she said it's likely the Igarashi-gumi
were involved in the shootings.

636
00:42:34,023 --> 00:42:35,724
The Igarashi-gumi?

637
00:42:35,791 --> 00:42:38,193
They were likely distributing guns
made at the factory.

638
00:42:38,260 --> 00:42:41,163
But why was Dad complicit
in something like that?

639
00:42:42,031 --> 00:42:44,099
I want to ask you about Tagusari…

640
00:42:45,501 --> 00:42:47,369
Tagusari? What happened?

641
00:42:48,370 --> 00:42:52,374
He asked me about the shootings
in Yomogida Town 30 years ago.

642
00:42:53,809 --> 00:42:55,778
From 30 years ago?

643
00:42:55,844 --> 00:42:59,882
He said a colleague
at Totsuka North was pursuing it,

644
00:42:59,948 --> 00:43:03,552
but apparently, Totsuka North
isn't handling any such case.

645
00:43:05,421 --> 00:43:06,955
Mr. Koike,

646
00:43:07,022 --> 00:43:10,526
do you know
what Tagusari is investigating?

647
00:43:13,896 --> 00:43:15,230
<i>Tsuda…</i>

648
00:43:15,297 --> 00:43:17,766
was probably investigating
the gun smugglers.

649
00:43:19,068 --> 00:43:21,603
If some kind of incident happened then…

650
00:43:26,175 --> 00:43:28,544
The ones who killed our parents

651
00:43:30,345 --> 00:43:31,914
might be the Igarashi-gumi.

652
00:43:38,487 --> 00:43:44,259
SIR, IS THIS REALLY GOOD ENOUGH?

653
00:43:53,502 --> 00:43:57,606
<i>-</i>Uno did it as revenge.
-Even though they forgot all about it.

654
00:43:57,673 --> 00:44:00,375
Why don't you stop carrying
the burden all by yourself?

655
00:44:00,442 --> 00:44:01,410
<i>To be honest…</i>

656
00:44:01,477 --> 00:44:02,978
I was scared of that.

657
00:44:03,045 --> 00:44:04,012
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.

